[% META title = 'Rake Back' %]

<div class="one">
  <p>We wish to reward players who become the first to join empty tables and get the most people in the game.</p> 

  <p>In order to do this we developed a rake back points system. Depending on your position at the table 
  and the number of players at the table you will get certain percentage of your rake back in the form of "points".
  Each point is equal to one chip and can be converted to chips once you reach the level of 100 points.</p>

  <p>Below you will find details on how to benefit most from the rake back system.</p>

  <p>First thing you need to know is how player position is calculated by the site. A position is calculated based on 
  the seat number. You can find seat numbers examples below. So if Alice takes seat #3, Bob - #6 and John - #8,
  Alice will be in 1st position, Bob - in 2nd and John - in 3rd.</p>

  <p>Below are a few examples of which seat is assigned to which number: <br /></p>
</div>

